The ham-fisted approach with which a case of two doctors in Limpopo has been dealt could lead to their colleagues across the country concealing their symptoms, if they were to contract the coronavirus. The South African Medical Association (SAMA) today said that doctors who are forced to be quarantined at a state facilities despite showing mild symptoms of Covid-19 might lead other health workers to hesitate in testing for the virus, particularly in Limpopo. Two doctors, who tested positive for the coronavirus but are asymptomatic, were carted off by a contingent of masked police to be quarantined at a tuberculosis...